New York
The international motion started out here Sept. 17, when thousands of humans protested in opposition to Wall Street earnings in two Manhattan . About 150 people stayed overnight in Zuccotti Park, a privately owned public area near Wall Street. Protesters have considering the fact that backed two rallies and marches addressing monetary inequity and other issues. More than 700 have been arrested as of Oct. 15.
Washington
Occupy D.C. started out Oct. 1 in McPherson Square, about two blocks from the White House. Some individuals clashed with police Oct. 8, which precipitated the closure of the National Air and Space Museum. Occupy organizers said they've scaled back every day protests and have begun to preserve 'teach-ins' on authorities corruption and money in politics.
Seattle
On the West Coast, Seattle protesters have occupied Westlake Park and City Hall Plaza seeing that late September; thousands have been routed and eight have been arrested in the metropolis Monday after defying the city's ban on tents in public parks. At least 3,000 human beings marched Saturday two to Pike Place Market, the place 200 sat down on First Avenue and blocked site visitors for about 10 minutes. Other Occupy protests




